All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Admin
Represents an Admin with access to system settings.
AdminController
Represents an AdminController which contains the logic for handling Admin data.
AdminUI
Represents the main menu user interface for an Admin, which can only be accessed by logging in with an admin account.
App
Starts the MOBLIMA Application.
Booking
Represents the Booking made by a moviegoer for a movie showing.
BookingController
Represents a BookingController which contains the logic for handling Booking data.
BookingUI
Represents the user interface for a moviegoer to make a booking for movie tickets.
Cinema
Represents a Cinema that belongs to a Cineplex.
Cineplex
Represents a Cineplex.
CineplexController
Represents a CineplexController which contains the logic for handling Cineplex data.
CRUDMovieListingUI
Represents the admin interface to create, update, delete, and list movies.
CRUDMovieShowingUI
Represents the admin interface to create, update, delete, and list movies.
DatabaseController<DataType>
Represents a DatabaseController which contains functions to read and write data of a specified data type from a database file.
Enumerators
Enumerators defined for readability and easier referencing.
Enumerators.Age
Enumerators to define the age category of the moviegoer.
Enumerators.CinemaClass
Enumerators to define the various cinema classes.
Enumerators.ContentRating
Enumerators to define the various movie content ratings.
Enumerators.Day
Enumerators to define the type of day a movie showing falls on.
Enumerators.MovieType
Enumerators to define the various movie types.
Enumerators.SeatStatus
Enumerators to define the various seat statuses.
Enumerators.ShowingStatus
Enumerators to define the various showing statuses.
Enumerators.User
Enumerators to define the various users.
Holiday
Represents a Holiday defined in the system settings.
HolidayController
Represents a HolidayController which contains the logic for handling Holiday data.
InputHandler
Represents the InputHandler used to take user input of various primitive or low-level datatypes.
ListTopMovies
Represents the user interface to list the top movies, used by both admin and moviegoer.
MainController
Represents a MainController containing database file paths and initializes starting data.
MainUI
Represents the main menu user interface for users to select if they are a moviegoer or admin.
Movie
Represents a Movie.
MovieController
Represents a MovieController which contains the logic for handling Movie data.
MovieController.MovieAttribute
Defined for readability and easier referencing of Movie attributes.
MovieGoer
Represents a MovieGoer.
MovieGoerUI
Represents the main menu user interface for a moviegoer.
PriceController
Represents a PriceController which contains the logic for handling Price data.
PriceType
Represents an empty interface implemented by classes that will affect the price of a movie ticket.
Review
Represents a Review added by a moviegoer to a movie.
SearchMovieUI
Represents the user interface to search for movies, used by both admin and moviegoer.
SearchShowingUI
Represents the user interface to search for showings, used by both admin and moviegoer.
Seat
Represents a Seat in the seating layout of a cinema.
SeatingLayout
Represents the SeatingLayout of a cinema.
Showing
Represents a Showing for a movie.
ShowingController
Represents a ShowingController which contains the logic for handling Showing data.
ShowingController.ShowingAttribute
Defined for readability and easier referencing of Showing attributes.
SystemConfigUI
Represents the admin interface to configure system settings related to holidays, ticket prices and admin accounts.
Ticket
Represents a Ticket for a showing.
UserHandler
Represents a UserHandler which is used to take user input of custom-defined datatypes.
